"src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25581,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/07\/wudu-ablution-hadath-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":25521,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Ablution required before prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 7, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cPrayer is not accepted from one in a state of minor impurity until he renews ablution.\u201d A man from Hadhramaut said, \u201cAbu Huraira, what is minor impurity?\u201d Abu Huraira said, \u201cIt is passing wind or gas.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25570,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/07\/light-sleep-not-nullify-ablution\/","url_meta":{"origin":25521,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Light sleep does not invalidate ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 7, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The companions of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would sleep lightly and then perform prayer without renewing ablution. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 376 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cThe scholars disagreed regarding ablution for one who slept. The majority\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25528,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/water-used-wudu-ghusl\/","url_meta":{"origin":25521,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Amount of water used for ablution, ritual bathing","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would perform ablution with one mudd, or half of a kilogram, and would perform a ritual bath with one sa\u2019, or two kilograms, up to five mudd. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 198, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 325 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":309,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/01\/04\/the-virtue-of-ablution-wudu\/","url_meta":{"origin":25521,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Ablution is radiance on Judgment Day","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 4, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira\u00a0reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"Verily, my nation will be called on the Day of Resurrection as brightly radiant from the traces of ablution. Whoever among you is able to extend his radiance, let him do so.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 136, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":41921,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2024\/05\/07\/wudu-clean-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":25521,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Cleansed of minor sins by ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 7, 2024","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Umamah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen a Muslim man performs ablution, his sins are removed from his hearing, his sight, his hands, and his legs. If he sits down, he will sit down forgiven.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 22171 Grade: Sahih li\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25521","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=25521"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25521\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=25521"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=25521"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=25521"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org